radiographic_examinations.findings: Thrombotic occlusion in the middle-through-distal portions of the right coronary artery and acute occlusion of the middle portion of the LAD artery consistent with very late stent thrombosis.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: The patient underwent PCI of the right coronary artery and the LAD artery, with stents placed. Follow-up cardiac ultrasound revealed nearly normal ventricular function before discharge, ejection fraction later declined to 34% due to congestive heart failure, but improved to 43% after treatment.
